Mr. C. F. W. Deitterich, a statistician and director of the
                    Statistical Department of Berlin, estimating the population
                    of the world at 1,300,000,000, sets down the Asiatic religions
                    as believed by 600,000,000 or about 46 per centpercent;
                    the Christian religion by 335,000,000, or about 25 per centpercent;
                    Pagans 200,000,000, or about 15 per centpercent; MohammedansMuslims,
                    160,000,000, or about 12 per centpercent. The 335,000,000 Christians
                    are again divided into 170,000,000 Roman Catholics,
                    or about 50 per centpercent; 89,000,000 Protestants, about 25 per centpercent;
                    and 76,000,000 Greek Catholics, about 22 per centpercent
